<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Chargé in the Soviet Union (
                        Kohler
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1050</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1050</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-04-23T06:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-04-23T06:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-23T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-23T06:00:00-05:00" n="1050" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1050">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Bacon, Leonard Lee: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kohler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-23T14:00:00+03:00">April 23, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 23—9:21 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1020. Still unable elicit answer Bacon visa, reDeptel 244, 21st.<note n="24" xml:id="d1050fn24">Same as telegram No. 709 to Shanghai, <ref target="#pg_867">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> Not informed of date Colling application but have sent note
                    Foreign Office. Doubtful Colling visa can be obtained prior next sailing <hi rend="italic">Smolny</hi>, exact date of which unknown here, but will
                    continue press.</p>
                <p>Repeated Shanghai 9, Dairen 22, Nanking 46.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kohler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
